1770183043.notes: sbs_entries_since_self_improve returns the just-started self-improve entry as the boundary, yielding 0 entries. The tool should find the PREVIOUS self-improve cycle's entry, not the current one. This forced manual workaround (reading L2 summaries to find the timestamp boundary). Fix: filter to self-improve entries with is_final=true or phase_end transition, excluding the current active session.

1770184492.notes: During /task alignment, exploration should precede user questions. I asked "do you have Chrome MCP?" when I could have checked .mcp.json myself. Explore-first produces better-informed questions and wastes fewer user interactions. Pattern: (1) explore landscape, (2) form understanding, (3) ask only what exploration can't answer.

1770187075.notes: sbs_serve_project MCP tool returns {running: false} without error details when it fails to start. The /qa skill had to fall back to manual Bash server startup, and initially guessed the wrong site directory (_site vs .lake/build/runway/). The serve tool should: (1) return an error message explaining WHY it failed, (2) know the correct site path from build artifacts, and (3) handle the .lake/build/runway/ path automatically.

1770193719.notes: MCP repo tests (forks/sbs-lsp-mcp) require project-specific venv to run (.venv/bin/pytest) but the sbs_run_tests MCP tool only runs tests in dev/scripts. No standard way to run MCP repo tests from the orchestrator — had to manually find the venv path. Should add MCP repo test support to sbs_run_tests or document the venv path.

1770196715.notes: QA agents should read criteria.py and TEST_CATALOG.md themselves rather than receiving pre-digested criteria in the prompt. The orchestrator should give high-level page assignments (e.g., "review the dependency graph, pdf, and paper") and agents infer the specific criteria, selectors, and interactive elements from the source files. This reduces orchestrator prompt size and keeps agents grounded in the actual criteria definitions.

1770197392.notes: Background agents completed but did not trigger the top-level chat to resume automatically. The orchestrator had to be manually prompted twice to check on agent status. Need a mechanism (or clearer protocol) for the orchestrator to block-wait on agent completion rather than relying on the user to prompt "check again". Consider using TaskOutput with block=true instead of run_in_background, or establishing a polling pattern that doesn't require user nudges.

1770211466.notes: Converge iteration 1 on GCR: 87/88 applicable criteria passed (98.9%). Single persistent failure is modal_content on dep_graph -- the theorem_thmcontent div in node modals is empty because the Dress pipeline generates HTML without populating LaTeX statement text. This is an upstream Lean generation issue, not fixable at CSS/JS level. 11 chapter criteria (brackets, tokens, tactic toggles, zebra striping) correctly skipped as N/A since GCR Lean content is reference comments only.

1770214074.notes: Converge iteration 1 on SBSTest: 83.8% pass rate (83/99). Only 2 of 16 failures are CSS-fixable (zebra striping). The dominant failure mode (11 criteria) is the Dress artifact pipeline not generating per-declaration HTML/hover files -- this is an upstream build issue requiring Lean/Dress changes, not CSS/JS. The 4 paper_tex failures are content-authoring gaps. The convergence loop cannot reach 100% without fixing the artifact pipeline (issue #184).

1770227300.notes: Build script cleans Dress build artifacts (including extract_blueprint binary) at the "Cleaning build artifacts" phase, then skips rebuilding Dress at "Building toolchain" because Lean sources are unchanged. This leaves extract_blueprint missing. The clean-then-skip sequence is a bug -- cleaning should be conditional on whether rebuild will follow, or extract_blueprint should be preserved across cleans.

1770227824.notes: sbs_build_project with --skip-cache still fails because --skip-cache only affects project caching, not toolchain caching. The toolchain source hash check runs independently and skips Dress/Runway rebuilds even after clean_artifacts() removed their binaries. Need either a --force-toolchain flag or conditional cleaning that preserves toolchain binaries when sources are unchanged.

1770229705.notes: Bash tool permissions are blocking rebuild operations during /converge execution phase. The orchestrator needs to delegate rebuild to sbs-developer agents or use MCP build tools, since direct shell commands for lake/python are denied by hooks. This creates friction in the rebuild-1 phase of convergence loop.

1770230504.notes: Some content does not yet load properly - seeing red text with yellow background that requires scrolling down to see. This suggests CSS/JS or lazy-loading issues where viewport-dependent content may not be initializing correctly on first render.

1770233469.notes: Extensive feedback session with multiple AskUserQuestion rounds on a complicated investigation task helped achieve clear alignment. Iterative clarification of scope, pain points, success criteria, and constraints through structured questions enabled shared understanding before planning.

1770237592.notes: Missed alignment gate - user said "move ahead through the gate" which was interpreted as plan approval to proceed directly to execution (branch creation, PR, phase transition). Should have explicitly confirmed plan approval with clear question before moving to execution phase.

1770239940.notes: Archive state persistence can become stale when sessions are interrupted - need protocol for state override when resuming tasks in earlier phases than archive indicates

1770240521.notes: Planning phase protocol should enforce EnterPlanMode tool usage for formal plan approval workflow, not just writing plan file directly

1770243545.notes: Issue body phrasing "Extract retrospection from end-epoch into separate introspection skill (becomes L0)" was unclear. Better framing: end-epoch delegates to introspect via gating system (like other skills do) rather than having custom retrospection logic - the retrospection was already introspection, just formalize the handoff.

1770278682.notes: When encountering system bugs during skill execution (like storage submodule in detached HEAD causing porcelain failures), should autonomously log issues via sbs_issue_log without waiting for user direction. This was a clear bug with error evidence - exactly the case CLAUDE.md describes for proactive bug logging.

1770281350.notes: When transitioning from /task finalization to /update-and-archive, the messaging should say "transitioning to end-epoch" rather than "handing off to update-and-archive" - clearer language that reflects what's actually happening (epoch boundary, not just skill handoff).

1770281709.notes: L2 introspection discovery phase returned 0 findings despite meaningful patterns existing in question_stats data. The threshold-based discovery heuristics didn't surface the header fragmentation or skill context gap issues - these required manual "dig deeper" exploration. Consider adding question pattern analysis to the automatic discovery phase, or lowering thresholds.

1770307707.notes: Issue handoff friction: When issues are created from conversation context, future sessions lack the reasoning trail. Solution: Include explicit archive/conversation references in issue bodies (e.g., "Created from session X, archive entry Y") so receiving agents can query the archive and read the full deliberation context. The phrase "aligned on in a previous chat" is helpful but could be machine-actionable with entry IDs.
